{"@context":"http://iiif.io/api/presentation/3/context.json","id":"https://digbmc.github.io/pta-manifests/phan/phan-03254/manifest.json","type":"Manifest","label":{"none":["PHAN-03254"]},"metadata":[{"label":{"none":["Timestamp"]},"value":{"none":["0:32:54"]}},{"label":{"none":["Film"]},"value":{"none":["Phantom Thread"]}},{"label":{"none":["Creator"]},"value":{"none":["Paul Thomas Anderson"]}},{"label":{"none":["Distance"]},"value":{"none":["close-up"]}},{"label":{"none":["Angle"]},"value":{"none":["eye-level"]}},{"label":{"none":["Location"]},"value":{"none":["interior"]}},{"label":{"none":["Movement"]},"value":{"none":["mobile, pan, tilt"]}},{"label":{"none":["Composition"]},"value":{"none":["single shot"]}}],"summary":{"none":["A woman sits at a table in a restaurant."]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03254/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"homepage":[{"id":"PHAN-03254","type":"Text","format":"text/html","label":{"none":["Object homepage"]}}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03254/canvas/1","type":"Canvas","height":1080,"width":1920,"label":{"none":["PHAN-03254"]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03254/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03254/canvas/1/annopage-1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03254/canvas/1/annopage-1/anno-1","type":"Annotation","motivation":"painting","target":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03254/canvas/1","body":{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03254/tiles/full/1920,1080/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":1080,"width":1920,"service":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03254/tiles","type":"ImageService3","profile":"http://iiif.io/api/image/3/level0.json"}]}}]}],"annotations":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03254/canvas/1/page/p1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03254/canvas/1/9e4a6ac8-3fea-46b4-977c-d403706f633f","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-30T14:04:18.216Z","creator":"g","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>PTA’s go-to direction for composer Jonny Greenwood was the word “romance.” He wanted the score to evoke a sense of dramatic romance that might not typically be associated with the Radiohead guitarist’s work. For inspiration, PTA showed Greenwood <em>The Passionate Friends</em> (1949). The director notes a curious coincidence: “‘Richard Addinsell, the composer of that score, was the lover of Victor Stiebel, a popular couture designer in London, so again there were those unexpected connections. Jonny would say that he would write music he imagined Reynolds would listen to’” (Bell, “<a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" class=\"Hyperlink SCXW188544411 BCX4\" href=\"https://www.bfi.org.uk/sight-and-sound/features/paul-thomas-anderson-phantom-thread-1950s-london-haute-couture-gothic-romance-daniel-day-lewis-vicky-krieps\"><u>Paul Thomas Anderson on Phantom Thread</u></a>”).&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03254/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:77.6699029126214,77.08737864077665,478.44660194174753,327.7669902912622"}}},{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03254/canvas/1/2206bcbe-9188-48d2-9bbd-ab1eae954d1e","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-30T14:04:31.664Z","creator":"g","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>According to the cinematography team, this scene, in which Reynolds and Alma walk to their corner table, was one of the very few that required digital cleanup after shooting due to the mirror on the wall (Lux Lighting, “<a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" class=\"Hyperlink SCXW168622415 BCX4\" href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=kpi393XkzUo\"><u>Lighting Phantom Thread</u></a>”).&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03254/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:1416.6990291262136,187.378640776699,416.31067961165036,579.4174757281553"}}}]}]}]}